# Approve PR Gate

When the `approve-pr` skill is used, enforce this workflow:

1. Run `review-open-pr` first for the same target PR.
2. Read the `review-open-pr` output categories.
3. Only proceed with approval when `all-good-lgtm` is `yes`.
4. If `all-good-lgtm` is `no`, ask the user whether to override approval.
5. Approve only if the user explicitly confirms override for that PR; otherwise keep approval blocked.

Approval rule:
- `all-good-lgtm: yes` -> approval allowed
- `all-good-lgtm: no` -> ask for explicit user override
- explicit user override -> approval allowed
